article.description: Taylor Stewart's layup with 15 seconds remaining in overtime gave Air Force a 66-65 win over TCU on Saturday.
article.headline: TCU comes up short vs. Air Force in overtime
article.linkText: TCU comes up short vs. Air Force in overtime
article.story: FORTH WORTH, Texas -- Taylor Stewart's layup with 15 seconds remaining in overtime gave Air Force a 66-65 win over TCU on Saturday. Stewart, who finished with four points, also pulled down the defensive rebound that set up the game-winning basket for the Falcons (12-8, 3-4 Mountain West). Derek Brooks led Air Force with 18 points on 6-of-8 shooting, and Michael Lyons scored 15, making 7 of 11 shots. Garlon Green had 16 points and nine rebounds for TCU (10-13, 1-7), and Amric Fields added 10 points. Air Force squandered a five-point lead over the final 2:37 in regulation, and after Green's jumper tied it at 58, neither team could score during the final 1:02 of the second half.
